470
00:32:08,120 --> 00:32:10,009
Have a seat right over there, please.

471
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:20,522
I'm Sergeant Taggart and this is
my partner, Detective Rosewood.

472
00:32:21,520 --> 00:32:24,205
You always treat visitors
from out of town like this?

473
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:30,881
Why didn't you identify yourself as a
police officer when you were arrested?

474
00:32:31,040 --> 00:32:34,123
'Cause I was mindin' my own business.
Where the fuck do you guys get off

475
00:32:34,280 --> 00:32:36,203
arrestin' somebody for gettin'
thrown out of a window?

476
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:38,647
We have six witnesses
that say you broke in

477
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:41,485
and started tearin' up the place,
then jumped out the window!

478
00:32:42,240 --> 00:32:45,289
And you guys believed that? What
the fuck are you, cops or doormen?

479
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:48,927
We're more likely to believe
an important local businessman,

480
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:51,082
than a foul-mouthed jerk
from out of town!

481
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:53,601
Foul-mouthed? Fuck you, man.

482
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:57,570
- Hey, Sarg.
- You watch your mouth.

483
00:32:57,720 --> 00:32:59,722
Don't square off on me
with some bullshit.

484
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:01,609
- You want to start some static?
- Don't push me!

485
00:33:01,760 --> 00:33:03,728
- Fuck you, man.
- [grunts]

486
00:33:03,880 --> 00:33:05,041
Ta

487
00:33:06,720 --> 00:33:08,085
Yes, sir?

488
00:33:09,200 --> 00:33:10,247
Come here.

489
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:17,090
[indistinct murmuring]

490
00:33:26,720 --> 00:33:28,006
Sir...

491
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:31,088
I apologize for striking you.

492
00:33:32,920 --> 00:33:34,331
I have no excuse.

493
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:39,125
Forget about it.

494
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:44,127
Detective Foley, I'm Lieutenant Bogomil,
of the Beverly Hills Police Department.

495
00:33:44,280 --> 00:33:46,282
Do you wish to file charges
against Sergeant Taggart?

496
00:33:48,880 --> 00:33:50,405
This is some kind of joke, right?

497
00:33:50,560 --> 00:33:54,724
Do you wish to file charges
against this officer for assault?

498
00:33:54,880 --> 00:33:58,487
Look, where I'm from, cops don't
file charges against other cops.

499
00:33:59,360 --> 00:34:02,125
No, I don't wanna do that.

500
00:34:02,280 --> 00:34:04,886
Well, in Beverly Hills,
we go strictly by the book.

501
00:34:06,280 --> 00:34:09,170
Now, why didn't you inform us
when you came to town?

502
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:11,926
- I'm on vacation.
- Well, if you're on vacation,

503
00:34:12,080 --> 00:34:14,560
what business did you have
in Victor Maitland's office?

504
00:34:14,720 --> 00:34:15,846
I had to go to the bathroom.

505
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:18,287
I was walkin' by, it looked like
a nice clean place, so I stopped.

506
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:22,809
You always take your gun on vacation?

507
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:25,611
I don't know,
I never been on vacation before.

508
00:34:25,760 --> 00:34:28,809
But in Detroit, cops are required
to carry a firearm at all times.

509
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:31,446
Well, if you wanna carry a gun,
I suggest you go back there.

510
00:34:31,600 --> 00:34:34,206
I really can't wait to get back there,
if you wanna know the truth.

511
00:34:34,360 --> 00:34:35,486
Is that so?

512
00:34:35,640 --> 00:34:38,007
I just got off the phone
with an Inspector Todd in Detroit.

513
00:34:38,160 --> 00:34:40,128
Does that name ring a bell?

514
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:43,841
He's my boss.

515
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:46,924
He tells me you might not
be very welcome back there.

516
00:34:48,640 --> 00:34:51,689
He says that you're
an outstanding young detective.

517
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:54,366
I find that very difficult to believe.

518
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:55,726
But it's true, though.

519
00:34:55,880 --> 00:34:58,531
He also says they nearly had
to fire you for insubordination.

520
00:34:58,680 --> 00:35:01,411
I find that very easy to believe.

521
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:04,203
Now, what are you doing
in Beverly Hills?

522
00:35:04,360 --> 00:35:06,681
I told you, I'm on vacation.
I went to the bathroom,

523
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:09,207
the next thing I knew six guys
threw me out a window.

524
00:35:09,360 --> 00:35:12,523
Inspector Todd gave me
a message for you, wanna hear it?

525
00:35:13,440 --> 00:35:14,601
I don't think so.

526
00:35:14,800 --> 00:35:17,406
He says if you're out here
investigating the Tandino murder,

527
00:35:17,560 --> 00:35:19,881
you needn't bother coming back.

528
00:35:20,040 --> 00:35:22,964
He tells me that if we inform him
you are working on this case,

529
00:35:23,120 --> 00:35:25,964
he'll have you brought up
on charges and fired.

530
00:35:26,880 --> 00:35:29,247
Now, one last time,
what are you doing...

531
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:32,961
- I'm on vacation!
- Vacation! Vacation.

532
00:35:33,120 --> 00:35:38,729
Rosewood, take Mr. Foley over to the
courthouse and let him arrange for bail.

533
00:35:39,720 --> 00:35:41,290
Would you follow me, sir?

534
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:46,005
You know, I gotta hand it to you guys,
if anything you are extremely polite.

535
00:35:47,720 --> 00:35:49,882
Pretty good punch
you got there, Taggart.

536
00:35:54,440 --> 00:35:55,851
[Axel] After you.

537
00:35:57,240 --> 00:35:58,765
After you.

538
00:36:00,120 --> 00:36:02,122
You guys are so sweet, you know that?

539
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:05,206
Thanks for bailin' me out, Jen.

540
00:36:05,360 --> 00:36:08,409
If I'd known why you'd been arrested,
I wouldn't have come.

541
00:36:08,600 --> 00:36:10,762
[chuckling] Oh, you don't mean that.

542
00:36:11,560 --> 00:36:13,210
No, I don't mean that.

543
00:36:13,920 --> 00:36:17,049
Axel, if it wasn't for Victor Maitland,
I'd be waiting on tables!

544
00:36:17,200 --> 00:36:19,282
It just so happens
that the day Mikey got killed,

545
00:36:19,440 --> 00:36:22,410
he showed up at my apartment
with a bag of German bearer bonds.

546
00:36:22,560 --> 00:36:24,722
I think he stole 'em
from whoever had him killed.

547
00:36:24,880 --> 00:36:26,166
When I mentioned Mikey's name,

548
00:36:26,320 --> 00:36:27,924
Maitland went nuts
and had me thrown out.

549
00:36:28,120 --> 00:36:29,645
Axel, you look like a hoodlum.

550
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:32,485
You go barging into his office
without an appointment.

551
00:36:32,640 --> 00:36:33,766
You're carrying a gun.

552
00:36:33,960 --> 00:36:37,123
If you barged into my office and
I didn't know you, I'd throw you out.

553
00:36:37,280 --> 00:36:38,611
Is this your car?

554
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:41,963
Oh, no, in Beverly Hills we just
take whichever car's closest.

555
00:36:42,120 --> 00:36:46,284
I remember you used to drive
that crappy, blue Chevy Nova.

556
00:36:47,680 --> 00:36:49,125
What are you driving now?

557
00:36:49,800 --> 00:36:52,883
- The same crappy, blue Chevy Nova.
- [laughing]

558
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:54,485
You think it's too late
for me to study art?

559
00:36:54,640 --> 00:36:55,880
Yeah, I do.

560
00:36:56,680 --> 00:36:59,843
Axel, why were you bothering Victor?

561
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:02,321
You don't think he has anything to do
with Mikey getting killed?

562
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:06,849
Oh, no. No, I was just pokin' around
I don't think he did nothin'.

563
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:10,447
Axel, Victor Maitland
is one of the top art dealers

564
00:37:10,600 --> 00:37:13,410
in the United States.
He has been for ten years.

565
00:37:13,560 --> 00:37:15,130
I'm impressed.

566
00:37:20,080 --> 00:37:24,005
- What are you looking back there for?
- The cops, they're following us.

567
00:37:24,160 --> 00:37:26,731
What? Where?

568
00:37:27,640 --> 00:37:31,008
In the back on the right.
The beige Ford.

569
00:37:59,520 --> 00:38:01,045
Can you believe this place?

570
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:04,446
Axel, how can you afford this?

571
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:06,728
They're only charging me
the single room rate.

572
00:38:06,880 --> 00:38:08,041
How can you afford that?

573
00:38:08,200 --> 00:38:11,170
Actually I can't afford it. But you know
what they got inside that bathroom?

574
00:38:11,320 --> 00:38:14,244
They got little robes,
with little initials of the hotel on it.

575
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:16,562
I love this place,
I can't leave this shit.

576
00:38:16,720 --> 00:38:18,051
I'm gonna steal one of them robes.

577
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:19,440
- You want one?
- No, thanks.

578
00:38:19,600 --> 00:38:20,761
- You want slippers?
- No.

579
00:38:20,920 --> 00:38:23,400
I'm gonna steal them, too.
You should take some of this shit.

580
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:25,164
Excuse me two seconds.

581
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:29,725
Hello, room service?

582
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:33,885
Yes, this is Mr. Axel Foley
in suite 1035. Yeah.

583
00:38:34,080 --> 00:38:36,401
I'd like to order something
from your late supper menu.

584
00:38:36,560 --> 00:38:39,769
But listen, I want you to deliver it to
this beige Ford parked out on Wilshire.

585
00:38:39,960 --> 00:38:44,045
Send down one
bay shrimp salad sandwich, OK?

586
00:38:45,320 --> 00:38:48,881
Right, and is the cold poached
salmon in dill sauce tasty?

587
00:38:49,040 --> 00:38:51,008
OK, send one of those down, all right?

588
00:38:51,160 --> 00:38:53,606
And send down something for dessert.
Thank you very much.

589
00:38:53,760 --> 00:38:55,250
All right, thank you.

590
00:38:55,400 --> 00:38:58,051
You're quite a sport.

591
00:38:58,200 --> 00:38:59,884
How long are you gonna stay?

592
00:39:01,040 --> 00:39:03,486
I'm gonna be in town
until I find out who killed Mikey.

593
00:39:05,920 --> 00:39:08,890
And I'm very seriously considering
going down to that warehouse

594
00:39:09,040 --> 00:39:10,929
where he worked
and checkin' that place out.

595
00:39:11,080 --> 00:39:14,448
Oh, really?
And how are you planning on getting in?

596
00:39:14,600 --> 00:39:16,523
[both chuckling]

597
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:37,007
- Good evening, sir.
- What the hell is that?

598
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:39,640
It's late supper, sir,
compliments of Axel Foley.

599
00:39:39,800 --> 00:39:43,282
Foley? How did he know we were here?

600
00:39:43,480 --> 00:39:44,970
'Cause I let you drive.

601
00:39:45,120 --> 00:39:46,929
I need a couple bananas,
how much are they?

602
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:49,321
Well, the buffet plate is $12.50.

603
00:39:49,480 --> 00:39:52,802
You get peaches, plums,
oranges and bananas.

604
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:54,769
All I need is a couple of bananas.

605
00:39:59,920 --> 00:40:02,446
Shh. Go ahead, take those bananas.

606
00:40:03,280 --> 00:40:04,361
Thanks.

607
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:08,084
Forget it, I'm not eatin' that.
Take it back.

608
00:40:08,240 --> 00:40:10,561
- [man] Certainly, sir.
- This really looks great.

609
00:40:24,680 --> 00:40:26,444
Can I get some extra mayo?

610
00:40:26,600 --> 00:40:27,931
- Certainly, sir.
- Thank you.

611
00:40:29,280 --> 00:40:30,805
- [Axel] Ready to go?
' [Jenny] Yeah.

612
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:34,681
There's the Mercedes.
Will you get rid of that stuff?

613
00:40:47,960 --> 00:40:50,406
[car sputters, stalls]

614
00:40:50,560 --> 00:40:51,971
[Taggart] What the hell are you doing?

615
00:40:52,120 --> 00:40:53,884
[engine turning over]

616
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:05,400
This the place?

617
00:41:05,560 --> 00:41:08,609
Yeah, but I'm still not sure
I should do this.

618
00:41:08,760 --> 00:41:10,046
OK, you don't have to do anything.

619
00:41:10,200 --> 00:41:12,043
But when you hear glass
and shit breaking,

620
00:41:12,240 --> 00:41:15,608
don't get scared, it's just me
kickin' in the window. Sit tight.

621
00:41:15,760 --> 00:41:17,000
[Jenny laughing]

622
00:41:17,200 --> 00:41:19,362
All right, come on, Axel.

623
00:41:42,520 --> 00:41:43,806
What's happenin', baby?

624
00:41:43,960 --> 00:41:45,724
[laughing] Axel, grow up.

625
00:41:58,880 --> 00:41:59,961
[sniffs]

626
00:42:00,160 --> 00:42:02,322
- You find something?
- Coffee grounds.

627
00:42:03,440 --> 00:42:04,601
$0'?

628
00:42:05,800 --> 00:42:07,643
You know what this stuff is used for?

629
00:42:07,800 --> 00:42:10,451
Yes, some people filter hot water
through it and drink it.

630
00:42:10,600 --> 00:42:12,438
Yeah, I'm gonna take this home
and filter hot water through it

631
00:42:12,439 --> 00:42:13,680
and drink it in the mornin'.

632
00:42:13,880 --> 00:42:15,803
- [laughs]
- [mimics laugh]

633
00:42:15,960 --> 00:42:17,849
[both laughing]

634
00:42:28,800 --> 00:42:30,404
- [whispers] What are we hiding for?
- Shh.

635
00:42:31,280 --> 00:42:33,601
I tell you, I wish you'd been
with me last night.

636
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:35,881
[man] What happened?

637
00:42:36,040 --> 00:42:38,884
[man 2] I stopped at a joint on the way
home to have a couple of drinks.

638
00:42:39,040 --> 00:42:41,884
- [man] Yeah. Which one?
- [man 2] One of the local joints.

639
00:42:42,080 --> 00:42:45,641
This guy comes in, he sits down
a couple of stools away.

640
00:42:45,800 --> 00:42:49,771
He's got one of them eyes
that's goin' like this.

641
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:53,123
I didn't know if he was tryin'
to put the make on me, or what.

642
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:55,044
So I thought I'd take you
over there tonight.

643
00:42:55,200 --> 00:42:58,204
Let him have a little shot at you
before I tore his head off.

644
00:43:08,800 --> 00:43:11,087
[sighs] Come on, let's go,
I wanna get outta here.

645
00:43:11,760 --> 00:43:13,683
Why don't you get off my back.

646
00:43:13,840 --> 00:43:14,921
Come on.

647
00:43:19,120 --> 00:43:20,406
I got it.

648
00:43:37,400 --> 00:43:39,880
- Axel, what the hell's going on?
- I'll tell you later, come on.

649
00:43:41,440 --> 00:43:43,124
- Hurry up
- "Hurry up

650
00:43:43,280 --> 00:43:46,090
- Gimme the key, I'm gonna follow 'em.
- You ever driven a Mercedes before?

651
00:43:46,240 --> 00:43:48,561
No, but a car is a car.
I drive my car everyday.

652
00:43:48,720 --> 00:43:50,529
I'm driving, I've seen your car.

653
00:43:50,680 --> 00:43:52,842
Oh, shit, that's cold.

654
00:43:53,960 --> 00:43:55,689
[car starts]

655
00:43:57,000 --> 00:43:58,843
[brakes squeal]

656
00:44:00,240 --> 00:44:01,890
A banana in your tailpipe!

657
00:44:02,040 --> 00:44:04,884
How could you not notice a man
sticking a banana in your tailpipe?

658
00:44:05,040 --> 00:44:07,122
- He distracted us, sir.
- And how'd he do that?

659
00:44:07,280 --> 00:44:10,887
He sent us a late supper, sir.
See, this waiter comes over...

660
00:44:11,080 --> 00:44:13,082
Billy, he gets the point.

661
00:44:13,240 --> 00:44:15,129
A late supper.

662
00:44:16,080 --> 00:44:17,684
And what did you have, Rosewood?

663
00:44:19,080 --> 00:44:23,563
I think it was a shrimp
salad sandwich, sir.

664
00:44:23,760 --> 00:44:26,764
- A shrimp salad sandwich.
- Yes, sir.

665
00:44:30,040 --> 00:44:33,487
I want you two to go back to the hotel
and wait for Foley to show up.

666
00:44:34,160 --> 00:44:37,926
And if you lose him again,
don't bother calling in. You got that?

667
00:44:38,080 --> 00:44:40,447
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

668
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:43,609
"A late supper."

669
00:44:45,720 --> 00:44:47,529
We've got something for you, Billy.

670
00:44:49,160 --> 00:44:51,288
An anti-banana disguise.

671
00:44:55,240 --> 00:44:56,571
It may come in handy.

672
00:44:56,720 --> 00:44:58,927
A little extra protection, Billy.

673
00:44:59,080 --> 00:45:00,411
[chuckling]

674
00:45:00,560 --> 00:45:02,085
Very funny.

675
00:45:04,040 --> 00:45:06,771
[sighs] Come on, Billy, let's go.

676
00:45:21,120 --> 00:45:23,327
Why don't you take the car
and go on home?

677
00:45:24,040 --> 00:45:27,487
- Well, what about you?
- I wanna find out what this place is.

678
00:45:27,640 --> 00:45:30,291
[Jenny] Oh, I can tell you that.
It's a bonded warehouse.

679
00:45:30,440 --> 00:45:33,489
They hold our foreign shipments here
until they clear Customs.

680
00:45:33,640 --> 00:45:36,246
Well, I'm gonna go check it out.
Just take the car and go home, OK?

681
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:40,325
Damn it, Axel!
I'm not gonna bail you out again.

682
00:45:40,480 --> 00:45:41,641
Go home.

683
00:46:38,720 --> 00:46:41,883
How you doin'? Could you come here
for a second, please?

684
00:46:43,560 --> 00:46:46,325
- Hi, do you have a match?
- There's no smoking in here.

685
00:46:46,480 --> 00:46:48,403
I'm not gonna smoke now,
I'm gonna smoke when I go outside.

686
00:46:48,560 --> 00:46:50,244
Thank you very much. Thank you.

687
00:46:50,400 --> 00:46:52,801
- Is your supervisor here?
- Yeah, he's in the office.

688
00:46:52,960 --> 00:46:54,849
- Can you get him for me?
- What's the problem?

689
00:46:55,040 --> 00:46:56,087
- You security here?
- Yeah.

690
00:46:56,240 --> 00:46:59,608
Then you're the fuokin' problem,
go get your supervisor, please. Now!

691
00:47:00,400 --> 00:47:02,528
- Now!
- OK.

692
00:47:09,920 --> 00:47:11,365
He didn't come back yet.

693
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:14,284
[sighs]

694
00:47:14,960 --> 00:47:16,530
Well, what do we do now?

695
00:47:17,680 --> 00:47:18,920
We wait.

696
00:47:22,520 --> 00:47:23,567
OK.

697
00:47:23,720 --> 00:47:26,326
- Can I help you'?
- Are you the supervisor here?

698
00:47:26,480 --> 00:47:27,447
Yes, who are you?

699
00:47:27,600 --> 00:47:29,921
I'm Inspector Rafferty,
United States Customs Service.

700
00:47:30,080 --> 00:47:32,287
Has all this stuff
passed through Customs already?

701
00:47:32,440 --> 00:47:33,601
No, this is the bonded area.

702
00:47:33,760 --> 00:47:35,524
Then tell me something.
Answer a question.

703
00:47:35,680 --> 00:47:38,763
How can a black man, dressed like me,
just march into your warehouse,

704
00:47:38,960 --> 00:47:40,610
walk into the bonded area
and start poking around

705
00:47:40,760 --> 00:47:43,127
without anyone askin' me
any questions whatsoever?

706
00:47:44,200 --> 00:47:45,531
Well, I don't know.

