Hi, Victor.

940
01:04:15,680 --> 01:04:17,284
I'm back.

941
01:04:24,040 --> 01:04:25,963
Look, cuz, don't even try it, OK?

942
01:04:27,280 --> 01:04:29,806
Why don't you get the hell
outta here, cuz.

943
01:04:29,960 --> 01:04:32,008
Get the fuck away from me.

944
01:04:42,880 --> 01:04:44,405
[mouths]

945
01:04:48,560 --> 01:04:49,891
That's very good, Victor.

946
01:04:50,040 --> 01:04:52,964
Could you teach him to roll over
and sit and do all that shit, too?

947
01:04:54,160 --> 01:04:56,561
- What do you want?
- I want to talk to you.

948
01:04:56,720 --> 01:04:58,643
Last time we met,
I didn't get a chance to talk to you.

949
01:04:59,440 --> 01:05:03,001
- I have nothing to say to you.
- That's cool, I'll do all the talking.

950
01:05:05,040 --> 01:05:07,611
This is a very nice place, Vic.

951
01:05:07,760 --> 01:05:10,604
Hi. I like this, this is nice.

952
01:05:11,640 --> 01:05:13,802
Glad you like it.
I must make you a member.

953
01:05:17,200 --> 01:05:21,125
You know, Victor, I know that you're
into a lot of crooked shit.

954
01:05:21,280 --> 01:05:24,568
And I have a pretty good idea
that you had Mikey killed.

955
01:05:25,480 --> 01:05:27,130
And when I find out for sure...

956
01:05:28,360 --> 01:05:30,362
...I'm gonna fuck you up real bad.

957
01:05:30,520 --> 01:05:31,521
Is that so?

958
01:05:32,840 --> 01:05:35,889
Now, listen to me,
my tough little friend.

959
01:05:36,040 --> 01:05:38,884
I don't know from under
what stone you crawled,

960
01:05:39,840 --> 01:05:43,401
or where you get these
ridiculous ideas about me,

961
01:05:44,120 --> 01:05:46,009
but it seems painfully obvious

962
01:05:46,160 --> 01:05:50,006
you haven't the slightest fucking
idea who you're dealing with.

963
01:05:51,200 --> 01:05:54,363
Now, my advice to you is...

964
01:05:54,520 --> 01:05:57,364
...crawl back to your
little stone in Detroit,

965
01:05:57,520 --> 01:06:01,366
before you get squashed, OK?

966
01:06:01,560 --> 01:06:03,528
Please step away from the table, sir.

967
01:06:03,680 --> 01:06:05,205
Gotta go now, Vic.

968
01:06:05,360 --> 01:06:07,761
- Nice meeting you again.
- Yeah.

969
01:06:08,880 --> 01:06:10,928
[handcuffs clicking]

970
01:06:14,400 --> 01:06:16,528
Catch you later, Vic.

971
01:06:16,680 --> 01:06:18,762
I can't wait.

972
01:06:31,920 --> 01:06:35,129
Don't I know you guys from some place?
You look so familiar.

973
01:06:37,600 --> 01:06:41,082
Detective Foley,
this is becoming very irritating.

974
01:06:41,240 --> 01:06:43,322
Why are you bothering Victor Maitland?

975
01:06:46,760 --> 01:06:50,446
I had a friend named Michael Tandino
that used to work for Victor Maitland.

976
01:06:50,600 --> 01:06:53,604
And Maitland had him killed.
I can't prove that right now,

977
01:06:53,760 --> 01:06:55,842
but when I do,
you'll be the first to know.

978
01:06:57,920 --> 01:07:00,890
Forget what you can prove.
Talk to me.

979
01:07:03,600 --> 01:07:06,444
OK, listen, everybody knows
that Victor Maitland

980
01:07:06,600 --> 01:07:08,125
is a hot-shot art dealer, OK?

981
01:07:08,280 --> 01:07:11,409
But I did some pokin' around and
art's not the only thing that he deals.

982
01:07:11,560 --> 01:07:14,404
I went to his warehouse
and I saw some guys unloading a crate

983
01:07:14,560 --> 01:07:16,767
that was filled
with German bearer bonds.

984
01:07:16,920 --> 01:07:20,163
Now, my friend Michael Tandino
had bonds like this on him,

985
01:07:20,320 --> 01:07:22,800
coincidentally,
when he was killed in Detroit.

986
01:07:22,960 --> 01:07:23,961
Just because Maitland chooses

987
01:07:24,120 --> 01:07:26,122
to invest in the same kind of bonds
your friend had,

988
01:07:26,280 --> 01:07:27,884
doesn't necessarily mean he's a killer.

989
01:07:28,040 --> 01:07:30,850
The man's not an investor,
he's a smuggler, OK?

990
01:07:31,000 --> 01:07:33,571
Be it bonds or drugs or whatever.

991
01:07:33,720 --> 01:07:36,326
The crate that I saw
didn't even pass through Customs.

992
01:07:36,480 --> 01:07:38,130
Maitland is paying someone so his guys

993
01:07:38,320 --> 01:07:40,971
can get the shipments out of Customs
before they get inspected.

994
01:07:41,160 --> 01:07:42,969
Maitland's guys get their hands on it,

995
01:07:43,160 --> 01:07:45,322
they take the drugs
or the bonds out of the crates

996
01:07:45,480 --> 01:07:48,563
and they send it back before
Customs even knows what's going on.

997
01:07:51,440 --> 01:07:52,930
And you witnessed all this?

998
01:07:53,080 --> 01:07:55,367
Everything except for the drugs,

999
01:07:55,520 --> 01:07:57,887
but I found coffee grounds
all over the warehouse.

1000
01:07:58,880 --> 01:08:00,006
Coffee grounds?

1001
01:08:00,160 --> 01:08:02,128
You said something about that before.
What does that mean?

1002
01:08:02,280 --> 01:08:04,601
Drugs are sometimes
packed in coffee grounds.

1003
01:08:04,760 --> 01:08:06,000
The scent throws off the dogs.

1004
01:08:06,160 --> 01:08:08,322
Very good, lieutenant.
Now what do we do?

1005
01:08:10,720 --> 01:08:12,529
Look, Detective Foley, I...

1006
01:08:13,840 --> 01:08:15,683
I'm sorry.

1007
01:08:15,840 --> 01:08:17,365
I'd really like to help you.

1008
01:08:18,280 --> 01:08:20,681
If you'd found the drugs,
that's one thing,

1009
01:08:20,840 --> 01:08:23,207
but if your only evidence
is coffee grounds,

1010
01:08:23,360 --> 01:08:24,964
we don't have enough
to get a search warrant.

1011
01:08:25,160 --> 01:08:26,844
Come on, guys,
I know how we can get around...

1012
01:08:27,040 --> 01:08:29,646
We don't get around search warrants
in Beverly Hills.

1013
01:08:31,600 --> 01:08:33,489
- Taggart.
- Yes, sir.

1014
01:08:33,640 --> 01:08:35,290
I want you to start checking this out.

1015
01:08:35,440 --> 01:08:39,047
Start with the LAPD, the FBI
and the Customs Service.

1016
01:08:39,200 --> 01:08:40,565
Hey, wait a minute, Taggart.

1017
01:08:40,760 --> 01:08:43,081
Look, lieutenant,
Maitland is much smarter than that.

1018
01:08:43,240 --> 01:08:44,890
We go and start
snoopin' around his place,

1019
01:08:45,040 --> 01:08:47,122
he's gonna close down and get
his shipments from someplace else.

1020
01:08:47,280 --> 01:08:49,567
- It'd be a big waste of time.
- Oh, really?

1021
01:08:49,720 --> 01:08:52,371
Is that what your extensive experience
leads you to believe?

1022
01:08:52,560 --> 01:08:54,767
- Look, I haven't been on your force...
- Sir!

1023
01:08:57,040 --> 01:08:58,201
Oh, shit.

1024
01:08:59,440 --> 01:09:02,444
- Is this the man?
- Yes, sir.

1025
01:09:03,440 --> 01:09:06,125
Is this the gentleman who crashed
through Victor Maitland's window?

1026
01:09:07,400 --> 01:09:11,121
Who disabled an unmarked unit
with a banana?

1027
01:09:11,280 --> 01:09:12,486
Yes, sir.

1028
01:09:12,640 --> 01:09:16,008
Who lured Taggart and Rosemont

1029
01:09:16,160 --> 01:09:19,562
into a gross dereliction of duty

1030
01:09:19,720 --> 01:09:22,530
at a striptease establishment?

1031
01:09:22,720 --> 01:09:24,245
It's Rosewood, sir.

1032
01:09:25,240 --> 01:09:26,480
Yes, sir.

1033
01:09:27,400 --> 01:09:32,042
Is this the gentleman who ruined the
buffet at the Harrow Club this morning?

1034
01:09:33,040 --> 01:09:34,769
[Bogomil] Yes, sir.

1035
01:09:34,920 --> 01:09:39,721
I just bet you are the pride
of your department in Detroit.

1036
01:09:43,720 --> 01:09:46,929
Lieutenant, I'd like to see you
in your office.

1037
01:09:47,840 --> 01:09:49,285
Yes, sir.

1038
01:09:53,200 --> 01:09:54,964
[mocking] ls this the man who...

1039
01:09:55,680 --> 01:09:58,251
...wrecked the buffet
at the Harrow Club this morning?

1040
01:09:58,400 --> 01:10:00,243
[Taggart] Lower your voice,
for Christ's sake.

1041
01:10:00,400 --> 01:10:02,562
Why, can the guy hear me
through the wall?

1042
01:10:02,760 --> 01:10:04,046
[all] Yes, he can.

1043
01:10:20,600 --> 01:10:25,925
Rosewood, take Detective Foley
back to his hotel room,

1044
01:10:26,080 --> 01:10:29,801
watch him pack,
and escort him to the city limits.

1045
01:10:31,320 --> 01:10:33,527
When you get there,
you can give him his gun back.

1046
01:10:34,920 --> 01:10:39,323
The two charges of disturbing the peace
have been dropped against you.

1047
01:10:39,480 --> 01:10:42,324
But the chief says if you return
to the city of Beverly Hills,

1048
01:10:42,480 --> 01:10:44,881
the charges will be reinstated

1049
01:10:45,040 --> 01:10:47,520
and you will be prosecuted
to the limit of the law.

1050
01:10:48,240 --> 01:10:49,685
Sir, may I say something?

1051
01:10:49,840 --> 01:10:51,080
- [Taggart] Billy...
- What?

1052
01:10:51,240 --> 01:10:53,163
Well, he seems to have enough
to follow up...

1053
01:10:53,320 --> 01:10:55,004
You wanna tell that to the chief?

1054
01:10:56,560 --> 01:10:59,404
- No, sir.
- Then I suggest you get moving.

1055
01:11:01,520 --> 01:11:02,681
Come on, Axel.

1056
01:11:22,360 --> 01:11:25,364
Right. Let me check on that
tomorrow and get right back to you.

1057
01:11:25,520 --> 01:11:26,851
Thank you.

1058
01:11:27,320 --> 01:11:29,800
- Hi.
- Victor, hi.

1059
01:11:29,960 --> 01:11:32,088
Sit down.
Hope I'm not interrupting you.

1060
01:11:33,040 --> 01:11:34,565
Of course not, don't be silly.

1061
01:11:35,280 --> 01:11:37,806
Jenny, there's a gentleman
in town from Detroit

1062
01:11:37,960 --> 01:11:40,930
who says he's a friend
of Michael Tandino.

1063
01:11:41,880 --> 01:11:45,601
He came by the office yesterday
and asked me all sorts of...

1064
01:11:45,760 --> 01:11:48,286
...rather odd questions.
Excuse me, darling.

1065
01:11:48,440 --> 01:11:50,886
I believe his name is Foley.

1066
01:11:51,040 --> 01:11:54,408
Since you were such a good friend of
Michael, I was wondering if you were...

1067
01:11:54,560 --> 01:11:56,642
...perhaps familiar with the fellow?

1068
01:11:56,800 --> 01:11:59,644
Well, we... grew up
in the same neighborhood.

1069
01:11:59,800 --> 01:12:01,609
Really? Have you seen him lately?

1070
01:12:03,400 --> 01:12:06,006
He... he came in yesterday.

1071
01:12:06,160 --> 01:12:08,242
What, came by here?

1072
01:12:09,400 --> 01:12:10,606
Huh.

1073
01:12:11,800 --> 01:12:12,961
And?

1074
01:12:14,800 --> 01:12:18,850
He told me that... Mikey'd been killed.

1075
01:12:19,360 --> 01:12:22,091
Yes. Yes, I know.

1076
01:12:24,240 --> 01:12:27,449
- And then?
- That's it.

1077
01:12:27,600 --> 01:12:31,400
He left and...
I haven't seen him since.

1078
01:12:33,440 --> 01:12:36,569
You wouldn't, by any chance, know
where Foley's staying would you?

1079
01:12:36,720 --> 01:12:40,327
I have some information
which just might be helpful for him.

1080
01:12:43,560 --> 01:12:45,483
No, I have no idea.

1081
01:12:48,120 --> 01:12:49,690
[sighing] Yes

1082
01:12:50,640 --> 01:12:51,801
Yes.

1083
01:12:53,120 --> 01:12:54,360
Yes.

1084
01:12:55,200 --> 01:12:57,282
Well, I hope I didn't
disturb you too much.

1085
01:12:57,440 --> 01:12:59,568
Oh, no, no problem.

1086
01:12:59,720 --> 01:13:02,803
- We'll have dinner soon, yes?
- That would be lovely.

1087
01:13:02,960 --> 01:13:04,121
Take care.

1088
01:13:16,520 --> 01:13:18,090
Hey, Billy,
I read the manifest, all right?

1089
01:13:18,240 --> 01:13:20,607
They're expecting
another shipment in today.

1090
01:13:21,920 --> 01:13:23,649
- If Bogomil...
- Never mind Bogomil!

1091
01:13:23,800 --> 01:13:26,485
This is a chance to blow this case wide
open, the two of us, what do you say?

1092
01:13:26,640 --> 01:13:28,005
- Come on.
- Look, Axel...

1093
01:13:28,160 --> 01:13:30,322
I wish I could, but I can't!

1094
01:13:30,480 --> 01:13:34,087
- Why?
- Because Bogomil would kill me.

1095
01:13:37,880 --> 01:13:39,166
Billy...

1096
01:13:39,320 --> 01:13:41,926
I'm not going to drive you
to the art gallery, Axel.

1097
01:13:42,880 --> 01:13:44,530
It'll just take a couple of minutes!

1098
01:13:44,680 --> 01:13:46,682
My friend Jenny'll let us
in Maitland's warehouse.

1099
01:13:46,840 --> 01:13:48,968
We can be there when the shipment
comes in and nail 'em!

1100
01:13:49,120 --> 01:13:51,122
How can you be sure
if it'll be drugs, or something?

1101
01:13:51,320 --> 01:13:52,606
I got a hunch, OK?

1102
01:13:52,760 --> 01:13:56,526
It's a technique by which many crimes
outside of Beverly Hills get solved.

1103
01:13:57,600 --> 01:14:00,001
Why didn't you tell Bogomil
about this shipment?

1104
01:14:00,200 --> 01:14:03,283
Bogomil does everything by the book.
You know what I'm startin' to think?

1105
01:14:03,440 --> 01:14:05,568
That everybody
in this goddamn town is a robot.

1106
01:14:05,720 --> 01:14:07,927
This thing is very personal to me.

1107
01:14:10,360 --> 01:14:13,045
All they asked me to do
was drive you out of town.

1108
01:14:14,360 --> 01:14:16,283
Now, I'm gonna screw that up, too.

1109
01:14:18,000 --> 01:14:21,891
- [sighs] Boy.
- Billy. I love you.

1110
01:14:22,720 --> 01:14:24,245
I just fell in love with you.

1111
01:14:27,200 --> 01:14:30,886
Jenny, how you doing?
This is my good buddy, Billy Rosewood.

1112
01:14:31,040 --> 01:14:32,371
- This is Jenny Summers.
- Hi.

1113
01:14:32,520 --> 01:14:35,251
- Billy's a Beverly Hills cop.
- How do you do?

1114
01:14:35,400 --> 01:14:36,526
That's Serge.

1115
01:14:36,680 --> 01:14:40,401
Yo, Serge, will you
get my friend an espresso?

1116
01:14:40,560 --> 01:14:43,131
You want it with a lemon twist?

1117
01:14:43,280 --> 01:14:46,682
Uh... Yeah, sure, if it's no bother.

1118
01:14:46,840 --> 01:14:49,889
- No, don't be stupid.
- [chuckling]

1119
01:14:50,040 --> 01:14:53,522
Axel, Victor Maitland was here
asking questions about you today.

1120
01:14:53,680 --> 01:14:56,081
I'm telling you,
he was acting real weird.

1121
01:14:56,240 --> 01:14:59,244
The reason I came down is 'cause
I want to get back inside the warehouse.

1122
01:14:59,400 --> 01:15:02,483
- How 'bout I go with you?
- Jenny, come on, now.

1123
01:15:02,680 --> 01:15:05,763
You work here with Serge,
in a art gallery. You're not a cop.

1124
01:15:05,920 --> 01:15:07,888
Axel, if this has anything
to do with Mikey,

1125
01:15:08,040 --> 01:15:09,929
then I want to go
check it out for myself.

1126
01:15:10,080 --> 01:15:12,162
I don't have time to stand here
and argue with you.

1127
01:15:12,360 --> 01:15:15,045
Wait a second. Let me get my keys...

1128
01:15:15,200 --> 01:15:16,964
...and we'll argue on the way.

1129
01:15:20,680 --> 01:15:23,081
Billy, your job's just to sit
out here and observe things.

1130
01:15:23,240 --> 01:15:26,323
- Don't make a move until I get you.
- I don't see why I can't come in.

1131
01:15:26,480 --> 01:15:28,562
You can't go in
'cause you're a cop in this town.

1132
01:15:28,720 --> 01:15:31,200
You go in without probable cause,
they're gonna call it an illegal search.

1133
01:15:31,360 --> 01:15:33,761
You know that. Or didn't they
teach you that in cop school?

1134
01:15:33,960 --> 01:15:36,884
Sit tight. If I find some evidence
I'll come out and get you.

1135
01:15:37,040 --> 01:15:39,122
- But you can't just...
- But nothing. Just be cool.

1136
01:15:39,280 --> 01:15:42,648
If anything jumps off, I'll come
and I'll get you, all right? OK?

1137
01:15:42,800 --> 01:15:44,370
Thank you.

1138
01:15:45,240 --> 01:15:48,483
Any chance you're gonna give me that
key and let me go in there by myself?

1139
01:15:48,640 --> 01:15:50,005
No chance.

1140
01:15:51,720 --> 01:15:54,451
Fuck. Come on.

1141
01:16:40,360 --> 01:16:42,124
Looks like they been here already.

1142
01:16:42,320 --> 01:16:45,210
- What exactly are you looking for?
- This.

1143
01:16:45,360 --> 01:16:48,569
This is a crate from overseas,
hasn't passed through Customs yet.

1144
01:16:58,360 --> 01:16:59,771
[Jenny] What is that?

1145
01:17:10,640 --> 01:17:12,210
Coffee?

1146
01:17:12,360 --> 01:17:13,930
[Axel] Yeah, it's coffee on top.

1147
01:17:20,200 --> 01:17:21,690
But this ain't sugar.

1148
01:17:21,840 --> 01:17:24,525
- Go get Rosewood.
- Welcome to the party.

1149
01:17:49,920 --> 01:17:51,763
Seems we have guests.

1150
01:18:12,920 --> 01:18:14,888
How nice.

1151
01:18:15,080 --> 01:18:17,128
I do like surprises.

1152
01:18:29,120 --> 01:18:30,281
Jeannette.

1153
01:18:34,480 --> 01:18:39,122
I just can't tell you how disappointed
I am to find you here.

1154
01:18:39,280 --> 01:18:41,726
- Victor, listen I...
- Shut up!

1155
01:18:43,000 --> 01:18:45,162
I don't want to hear it.

1156
01:19:03,040 --> 01:19:06,647
Take her to the car
and wait for me, OK?

1157
01:19:06,840 --> 01:19:08,365
What are you gonna do with him?

1158
01:19:08,520 --> 01:19:13,242
I think you should be more worried
about what we're going to do with you.

1159
01:19:13,400 --> 01:19:16,085
Jenny, don't worry about me.
We got cocaine and coffee here.

1160
01:19:16,240 --> 01:19:18,163
We're gonna get wired
and have a big party.

1161
01:19:18,320 --> 01:19:20,766
Thanks for havin' me over Vic,
this is very nice.

1162
01:19:22,000 --> 01:19:23,889
You say something?

1163
01:19:32,000 --> 01:19:33,445
[sighs]

1164
01:19:38,600 --> 01:19:40,204
If somethin' happens to her...

1165
01:19:41,400 --> 01:19:42,765
Mm?

1166
01:19:43,400 --> 01:19:45,368
I'm all ears.

1167
01:19:46,840 --> 01:19:47,966
...I'll kill you.

1168
01:19:49,680 --> 01:19:50,841
Really?

1169
01:19:51,920 --> 01:19:53,365
That would be a neat trick.

1170
01:20:05,240 --> 01:20:06,924
Well, cuz.

1171
01:20:07,920 --> 01:20:09,570
Are you still pissed at me?

1172
01:20:11,400 --> 01:20:14,563
Oh, no. No.

1173
01:20:16,120 --> 01:20:18,202
But I should've taken care of you
in Detroit.

1174
01:20:24,080 --> 01:20:26,401
When I popped your little buddy.

1175
01:20:27,600 --> 01:20:29,967
[grunting]

1176
01:20:30,120 --> 01:20:32,691
[coughing]

1177
01:20:33,240 --> 01:20:34,810
Goodbye, Mr. Foley.

1178
01:20:37,320 --> 01:20:38,606
Have a nice day.

1179
01:20:39,320 --> 01:20:40,731
[gasping] I'll try.

1180
01:21:05,000 --> 01:21:07,321
[groans] Damn it.

1181
01:21:10,640 --> 01:21:12,130
Oh, boy.

1182
01:21:24,280 --> 01:21:28,410
How's that little bump on the head doin'
I gave you in Detroit, huh?

1183
01:21:28,560 --> 01:21:30,130
Healed up nice, I hope.

1184
01:21:32,800 --> 01:21:34,006
[grunting]

1185
01:21:34,200 --> 01:21:35,486
[coughing]

1186
01:21:40,920 --> 01:21:42,490
[Axel coughing]

1187
01:21:56,320 --> 01:21:57,321
Freeze!

1188
01:22:01,320 --> 01:22:02,321
[screams]

1189
01:22:11,360 --> 01:22:12,441
Thanks, man.

1190
01:22:23,400 --> 01:22:25,528
[tires screeching]

1191
01:22:27,560 --> 01:22:30,882
Tell Taggart to check out the warehouse
and act on whatever he finds.

1192
01:22:31,040 --> 01:22:32,201
I'll explain it to him later.

1193
01:22:32,360 --> 01:22:34,488
DD-6, Sergeant Taggart is here now,

1194
01:22:34,640 --> 01:22:36,369
<i>- and he wants to talk to you.</i>
- Shit!

1195
01:22:36,520 --> 01:22:39,444
Billy, what the hell is goin' on?

1196
01:22:39,640 --> 01:22:41,688
I'm sorry, Sarg, I can't talk now.

1197
01:22:41,840 --> 01:22:43,649
What you mean you can't talk now?

1198
01:22:43,800 --> 01:22:47,486
Just check out the warehouse and
please don't say anything to Bogomil.

1199
01:22:48,560 --> 01:22:50,608
Sorry, sir, he's not
transmitting any more.

1200
01:22:50,760 --> 01:22:51,921
- Ah, shit!
- What's the matter?

1201
01:22:52,080 --> 01:22:55,323
It's Billy, he's doin' somethin'
dumb again, but I don't know what.

1202
01:22:55,480 --> 01:22:56,925
Was he calling from the hotel?

1203
01:22:57,080 --> 01:22:58,570
No, sir.

1204
01:22:59,400 --> 01:23:02,722
Right now his car is heading north
on Palm Canyon Road.

1205
01:23:02,880 --> 01:23:04,609
Hey, we were there this morning.

1206
01:23:04,760 --> 01:23:06,649
- [Taggart] What?
- Yeah.

1207
01:23:06,800 --> 01:23:09,041
Foley was up there,
looking over Maitland's house.

1208
01:23:09,200 --> 01:23:10,770
Do you have the address
of that warehouse?

1209
01:23:10,960 --> 01:23:12,086
Yes, sir.

1210
01:23:12,240 --> 01:23:15,562
Here. You two check that place out.

1211
01:23:15,760 --> 01:23:18,604
Then find me, and let me know
what the hell is goin' on over there.

1212
01:23:18,800 --> 01:23:20,689
And don't talk to anybody but me!

1213
01:23:32,880 --> 01:23:34,882
[car approaching]

1214
01:23:41,760 --> 01:23:43,967
Hold it right there, Foley,
you're under arrest.

1215
01:23:44,160 --> 01:23:45,446
Billy, what the hell are you doin' here?

1216
01:23:45,600 --> 01:23:47,120
I stole my gun and forced him
to bring me here.

1217
01:23:47,121 --> 01:23:50,363
No, he didn't, Sarg. Look, everything
he said about Maitland is right.

1218
01:23:50,520 --> 01:23:53,205
Now, he's kidnapped a woman
and he's got her in his house.

1219
01:23:54,320 --> 01:23:55,970
Well, let's go in there and get her.

1220
01:23:56,120 --> 01:23:57,724
What the fuck you think
I'm tryin' to do here?

1221
01:23:57,880 --> 01:24:01,202
You're not doin' anything! We'll have
a search warrant in 20 minutes.

1222
01:24:01,360 --> 01:24:04,204
- She'll be dead in 20 minutes.
- Stop workin' on that lock.

1223
01:24:04,360 --> 01:24:07,921
I'm gonna open this door and I'm goin'
inside. You wanna stop me? Shoot me.

1224
01:24:10,320 --> 01:24:11,924
- Me, too.
- Billy!

1225
01:24:12,080 --> 01:24:14,447
You can do what you want,
but I'm going in with Axel.

1226
01:24:14,600 --> 01:24:16,921
Goddamn it, Billy,
this is really serious trouble!

1227
01:24:17,080 --> 01:24:19,128
If you're lucky, you'll just get fired.

1228
01:24:19,320 --> 01:24:21,084
- [door opens]
- [Axel] Got it.

1229
01:24:21,280 --> 01:24:23,203
[Taggart] It's my last warning, Foley.

1230
01:24:29,280 --> 01:24:33,285
- Billy!
- I'm sorry, Sarg, I've got to.

1231
01:24:37,560 --> 01:24:40,291
Shit. Wait a minute.

1232
01:24:52,680 --> 01:24:55,001
- [beeping]
- [man] What's that?

1233
01:24:56,360 --> 01:24:59,170
Looks like east gate. Punch it up.

1234
01:25:03,320 --> 01:25:05,368
Who the hell is that?

1235
01:25:06,200 --> 01:25:07,645
Better get Maitland up here.

1236
01:25:24,480 --> 01:25:27,165
Where is everybody?
Owensby, is Rosewood back yet?

1237
01:25:27,320 --> 01:25:29,163
- No, sir.
- Have you seen Taggart?

1238
01:25:29,320 --> 01:25:31,129
He took off about ten minutes ago.

1239
01:25:41,240 --> 01:25:43,208
Foley's on the grounds.

1240
01:25:43,360 --> 01:25:45,169
Well, how the hell should I know?

1241
01:25:45,320 --> 01:25:47,163
Get some people out there right away.

1242
01:25:50,120 --> 01:25:52,168
Don't take your eyes off that screen.

1243
01:26:23,800 --> 01:26:26,121
I want you to try to locate
Taggart and Rosewood.

1244
01:26:37,240 --> 01:26:38,446
Come on.

1245
01:26:43,960 --> 01:26:45,530
[grunts]

1246
01:26:52,600 --> 01:26:54,250
[Taggart] OK, OK, OK.

1247
01:26:55,800 --> 01:26:58,041
[grunting] Shit.

1248
01:27:00,280 --> 01:27:01,964
[yelling]

1249
01:27:02,600 --> 01:27:05,968
- They must be away from the car, sir.
- I can see that, keep trying.

1250
01:27:07,240 --> 01:27:09,971
- DD-13, come in please.
- What's their 20?

1251
01:27:14,640 --> 01:27:17,962
- 609 Palm Canyon Road.
- Who lives at that address?

1252
01:27:21,880 --> 01:27:23,644
A Victor Maitland, sir.

1253
01:27:25,080 --> 01:27:27,162
[gasping] Try again.

1254
01:27:27,320 --> 01:27:28,685
Let's go around.

1255
01:27:29,800 --> 01:27:31,484
We can do it. Come on.

1256
01:27:36,680 --> 01:27:37,681
Ready?

1257
01:27:37,840 --> 01:27:39,808
One, two...

1258
01:27:41,400 --> 01:27:43,641
[grunting]

1259
01:27:47,280 --> 01:27:49,328
[Taggart grunting]

1260
01:27:49,480 --> 01:27:51,209
[chuckling]

1261
01:27:54,520 --> 01:27:56,568
[machine gunfire]

1262
01:28:11,240 --> 01:28:12,651
You all right?

1263
01:28:16,360 --> 01:28:18,203
What the fuck am I doin' here?

1264
01:28:25,000 --> 01:28:26,206
Drop it!

1265
01:28:35,560 --> 01:28:37,642
- Good shot, Billy.
- Let's go.

1266
01:28:39,160 --> 01:28:41,049
[machine gunfire]

1267
01:28:42,240 --> 01:28:43,969
[all grunting]

1268
01:28:48,560 --> 01:28:51,291
- Jesus Christ!
- Yeah, these guys are serious.

1269
01:28:51,440 --> 01:28:53,090
I hate machine guns.

1270
01:29:02,640 --> 01:29:04,005
Cover me.

1271
01:29:17,480 --> 01:29:19,767
You guys go around front,
I'm gonna check the back.

1272
01:29:22,720 --> 01:29:25,121
Sir, we have a report of shots fired
at that same location.

1273
01:29:25,280 --> 01:29:27,282
609 Palm Canyon Road.

1274
01:29:28,240 --> 01:29:31,244
Put out a 998: officers need assistance.

1275
01:29:31,400 --> 01:29:33,129
- Undercovers on the scene.
- Sir?

1276
01:29:33,280 --> 01:29:35,806
Just do it!
I want all north end units to roll.

1277
01:29:35,960 --> 01:29:38,327
South end units stay in their area.

1278
01:29:38,480 --> 01:29:40,084
Damn! Let's go.

1279
01:29:40,240 --> 01:29:42,083
Undercover officers at location.

1280
01:29:50,840 --> 01:29:52,968
Police! You're all under arrest!

1281
01:29:59,480 --> 01:30:02,245
You do that again,
I'll shoot you myself.

1282
01:31:10,480 --> 01:31:12,244
[spent shells clattering]

1283
01:31:14,320 --> 01:31:16,243
You know what I keep thinking about?

1284
01:31:17,520 --> 01:31:19,249
You know the end of <i>Butch Cassidy</i>?

1285
01:31:22,720 --> 01:31:25,564
Where Redford and Newman
are almost out of ammunition.

1286
01:31:27,840 --> 01:31:31,401
And the whole Bolivian Army
is out in front of this little hut.

1287
01:31:33,720 --> 01:31:35,245
Billy...

1288
01:31:36,760 --> 01:31:38,728
I'm gonna make you pay for this.

1289
01:32:26,280 --> 01:32:27,281
[gunshot]

1290
01:32:27,960 --> 01:32:30,247
[groaning]

1291
01:32:48,840 --> 01:32:51,650
[siren wailing]

1292
01:32:58,840 --> 01:33:00,763
- You gonna hang around here?
- Fuck no!

1293
01:33:12,280 --> 01:33:13,930
[tires screeching]

1294
01:33:28,200 --> 01:33:30,328
- Freeze it!
- Hold it right there.

1295
01:33:33,840 --> 01:33:35,171
[Bogomil] Oh, shit.

1296
01:33:47,880 --> 01:33:49,291
[Jenny] Axel!

1297
01:33:49,440 --> 01:33:51,761
[gasping]

1298
01:33:53,600 --> 01:33:56,444
Be careful, old boy, you might hit me.

1299
01:34:05,040 --> 01:34:06,041
Freeze!

1300
01:34:14,040 --> 01:34:15,485
[body thudding]

1301
01:34:24,080 --> 01:34:26,970
Police! You're all under arrest!

1302
01:34:27,120 --> 01:34:29,521
Lay down your weapons in front of you

1303
01:34:29,720 --> 01:34:33,247
and take two steps back
with your hands up!

1304
01:34:38,360 --> 01:34:39,566
Very good.

1305
01:34:40,400 --> 01:34:41,561
Great.

1306
01:34:41,720 --> 01:34:43,848
[indistinct radio chatter]

1307
01:34:51,080 --> 01:34:53,162
[indistinct murmuring]

1308
01:35:00,720 --> 01:35:02,245
What the hell's going on here?

1309
01:35:03,080 --> 01:35:04,127
Oh, shit.

1310
01:35:04,280 --> 01:35:06,442
- What's this man doing here?
- Bleeding, sir.

1311
01:35:06,600 --> 01:35:09,888
Rosewood, how come
he isn't wearing cuffs?

1312
01:35:11,280 --> 01:35:14,409
Well, he isn't actually in custody, sir.

1313
01:35:14,600 --> 01:35:17,285
Well, place him in custody,
or would you like me to do it?

1314
01:35:17,480 --> 01:35:19,721
Wouldn't you like to hear
my report first, sir?

1315
01:35:22,120 --> 01:35:24,851
You have a report
that explains all this?

1316
01:35:25,720 --> 01:35:26,801
Yes, sir.

1317
01:35:28,280 --> 01:35:31,329
Well, I will be very glad to hear it.

1318
01:35:33,480 --> 01:35:38,122
Well, sir, Ms. Jeannette Summers, the
manager of Mr. Maitland's art gallery,

1319
01:35:38,280 --> 01:35:40,760
accidentally discovered large quantities
of a substance

1320
01:35:40,960 --> 01:35:44,009
she suspected was cocaine
in the art gallery's warehouse.

1321
01:35:44,160 --> 01:35:47,164
She immediately communicated her
discovery to Detective Axel Foley

1322
01:35:47,320 --> 01:35:48,685
of the Detroit Police Force.

1323
01:35:50,520 --> 01:35:53,444
Detective Foley was,
at the time, cooperating

1324
01:35:53,640 --> 01:35:57,326
in a joint Beverly Hills-Detroit
investigation of narcotics trafficking.

1325
01:35:57,520 --> 01:36:01,081
Detectives Foley and Rosewood,
responding to Ms. Summers' report,

1326
01:36:01,240 --> 01:36:03,720
proceeded to the warehouse,
where Rosewood did, in fact,

1327
01:36:03,880 --> 01:36:06,451
discover approximately
80 kilos of cocaine.

1328
01:36:07,520 --> 01:36:09,682
Rosewood immediately
called for backup.

1329
01:36:09,840 --> 01:36:11,842
And I dispatched our officers
to this location.

1330
01:36:12,000 --> 01:36:15,322
Sergeant Taggart here,
was the first to arrive at the scene.

1331
01:36:15,480 --> 01:36:18,484
And having probable cause
to believe a felony was in progress,

1332
01:36:18,640 --> 01:36:22,531
Sergeant Taggart joined Rosewood,
with Detective Foley

1333
01:36:22,680 --> 01:36:26,446
present only as an observer,
and proceeded to enter the grounds.

1334
01:36:26,600 --> 01:36:28,284
And in the course
of defending ourselves,

1335
01:36:28,440 --> 01:36:31,523
we shot several suspects,
including Mr. Maitland.

1336
01:36:36,240 --> 01:36:39,005
You expect me to believe that report?

1337
01:36:40,280 --> 01:36:42,123
That's the report I'm filing, sir.

1338
01:36:45,400 --> 01:36:46,890
Sergeant Taggart...

1339
01:36:47,960 --> 01:36:49,962
Why don't you tell me what happened?

1340
01:37:03,440 --> 01:37:05,761
Happened just like
the lieutenant said, chief.

1341
01:37:17,880 --> 01:37:23,091
[chuckles] Well, I suppose
congratulations are in order.

1342
01:37:25,480 --> 01:37:27,209
Thank you, sir.

1343
01:37:27,400 --> 01:37:30,290
That report better be
on my desk in the morning.

1344
01:37:30,440 --> 01:37:32,283
Yes, sir, first thing.

1345
01:37:40,760 --> 01:37:43,081
You were lyin' your ass off.

1346
01:37:43,240 --> 01:37:44,446
[both laughing]

1347
01:37:46,760 --> 01:37:49,843
Why don't you go to the hospital
and get your shoulder looked at?

1348
01:37:51,120 --> 01:37:52,485
Excuse me, sir.

1349
01:37:57,960 --> 01:38:00,691
I was wondering if you could,
like, do me a favor, sir?

1350
01:38:01,920 --> 01:38:05,402
- I think your favors are all used up.
- I understand.

1351
01:38:05,560 --> 01:38:08,848
It's just that I was hopin'
you could call my Inspector Todd,

1352
01:38:09,000 --> 01:38:12,322
my boss back home and straighten
things out, but that's all right.

1353
01:38:12,480 --> 01:38:14,403
Guess I'm out of a job.
It's cool, though.

1354
01:38:14,560 --> 01:38:16,881
I think I'm gonna stay in Beverly Hills.
I like it here.

1355
01:38:17,040 --> 01:38:19,520
I'm gonna start my own
private investigation company.

1356
01:38:19,680 --> 01:38:21,091
How's that sound?

1357
01:38:21,240 --> 01:38:23,686
I will talk to Inspector Todd
first thing tomorrow.

1358
01:38:23,840 --> 01:38:25,365
- Will you, really?
- Yes, you bet.

1359
01:38:25,520 --> 01:38:27,761
- Thank you so much, sir.
- You're welcome.

1360
01:38:34,920 --> 01:38:37,969
How you doin'? I'm Axel Foley,
checkin' out of suite 1035.

1361
01:38:38,120 --> 01:38:40,646
One moment, sir.
I'll get your bill.

1362
01:38:42,600 --> 01:38:45,524
- [Taggart clears throat]
- Hey! Guys!

1363
01:38:45,680 --> 01:38:48,968
You all didn't have to see me off.
But I'm very moved by the gesture.

1364
01:38:49,120 --> 01:38:52,727
Bogomil ordered us
to make sure you got out of town.

1365
01:38:54,040 --> 01:38:56,520
You know, that doesn't even matter
to me, Billy. You know what matters?

1366
01:38:56,680 --> 01:38:57,966
That you guys came down here.

1367
01:38:58,160 --> 01:39:01,209
I'm all choked up on the inside
I got a lump in my throat.

1368
01:39:01,360 --> 01:39:04,170
You look a little misty yourself there,
Taggart.

1369
01:39:04,320 --> 01:39:06,163
- [man] There you go, sir.
- [Axel] Oh, thank you.

1370
01:39:06,320 --> 01:39:10,211
Excuse me. The Beverly Hills Police
Department is picking that up.

1371
01:39:10,360 --> 01:39:12,442
Oh, get outta here! Guys!

1372
01:39:12,600 --> 01:39:16,127
That's the last straw. That was
the last straw, you guys are too nice.

1373
01:39:16,280 --> 01:39:19,090
Sir, do you sell those
Beverly Palm robes down here?

1374
01:39:19,240 --> 01:39:21,049
Yes, we do sir,
they're $95 apiece.

1375
01:39:21,200 --> 01:39:23,123
Money is no object, put 'em on my tab.

1376
01:39:23,280 --> 01:39:24,930
I have to have two of them, though.

1377
01:39:27,040 --> 01:39:30,761
Billy, you saved my life, OK?

1378
01:39:30,920 --> 01:39:32,888
I don't think I'll ever
be able to repay you.

1379
01:39:33,040 --> 01:39:34,610
But as a token of my appreciation,

1380
01:39:34,760 --> 01:39:37,366
I want you to have this
fine Beverly Palm robe.

1381
01:39:37,520 --> 01:39:39,360
Each time you get out of the shower
and you're dripping wet,

1382
01:39:39,361 --> 01:39:42,079
for the rest of your life, I want you
to think about our friendship.

1383
01:39:42,080 --> 01:39:44,924
I want you to think about Axel Foley.
I love you, Billy.

1384
01:39:49,320 --> 01:39:51,891
- Thanks, Axel.
- [laughs]

1385
01:39:52,040 --> 01:39:56,364
Here, let me take this.
You should rest that arm.

1386
01:39:56,520 --> 01:39:58,727
Billy, take care of the tab, would you?

1387
01:39:59,520 --> 01:40:01,682
- Hey, Taggart.
- Here you are, sir.

1388
01:40:01,840 --> 01:40:03,604
This is for you.

1389
01:40:03,760 --> 01:40:06,604
No, that's all right.
You keep it as a souvenir.

1390
01:40:08,520 --> 01:40:10,522
I already have three of 'em in my bag.

1391
01:40:14,920 --> 01:40:16,410
- Here you go.
- Thank you, sir.

1392
01:40:16,560 --> 01:40:18,403
- Take it easy.
- You're not gonna say goodbye?

1393
01:40:19,600 --> 01:40:22,251
Why, ain't you guys gonna tail me
to the city limits, anyway?

1394
01:40:22,400 --> 01:40:25,927
- Yes, we are.
- I figured you would.

1395
01:40:26,120 --> 01:40:28,461
I was thinking about stopping off
and getting something to drink, though.

1396
01:40:28,520 --> 01:40:30,568
Yeah, we sorta figured you would.

1397
01:40:30,720 --> 01:40:32,231
That mean you guys
are gonna join me?

1398
01:40:32,280 --> 01:40:35,648
I don't think so, Axel,
we're still on duty.

1399
01:40:36,920 --> 01:40:40,129
Well, I don't think one beer's
gonna kill us, Billy.

1400
01:40:40,280 --> 01:40:43,363
That's right, listen to Taggart here.
Lighten up, all right?

1401
01:40:43,520 --> 01:40:46,091
One drink's not gonna kill us.

1402
01:40:46,240 --> 01:40:47,605
[♫ Patti LaBelle: <i>Stir It Up</i>]

1403
01:40:47,760 --> 01:40:48,886
[Axel] Hey, guys

1404
01:40:49,040 --> 01:40:51,646
If you fall too far behind,
don't be afraid to honk, OK?

1405
01:40:51,800 --> 01:40:53,484
Where we goin' anyway'?

1406
01:40:53,640 --> 01:40:56,086
Don't worry about it,
just follow my lead.

1407
01:40:56,240 --> 01:40:58,641
I know the perfect place.
You guys will love it.

1408
01:40:58,800 --> 01:41:00,040
Trust me.